HB 1231 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Berault
Abstract: Provides relative to Medicaid coverage for pregnant women.
Present law provides Medicaid coverage for continuous glucose monitoring for individuals
who require insulin more than two times daily or evidence level 2 or level 3 hypoglycemia.
Proposed law modifies present law providing Medicaid coverage for continuous glucose
monitoring for diabetes, including gestational diabetes, for individuals who require insulin
or evidence level 2 or level 3 hypoglycemia.
(Amends R.S. 46:450.8(A)(1))
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Health and Welfare to
the original bill:
1. Remove requirement for Medicaid coverage for dental services for pregnant
women.
2. Provide for continuous glucose monitoring for diabetes, including gestational
diabetes, for individuals who require insulin for the treatment of diabetes.
